  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to medium-high heat (400°F/200°C).",
    "Season the salmon fillets with salt and black pepper.",
    "In a small saucepan, combine honey, soy sauce, brown sugar, rice vinegar, ginger, and garlic. Bring to a boil over medium heat, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "Brush the lacquer glaze onto both sides of the salmon fillets.",
    "Add the salmon fillets to the preheated grill and cook for 4-6 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "Transfer the salmon to a plate and brush with additional lacquer glaze if desired.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and garnish with chopped parsley and sliced lemon wedges if desired.",
    "Let the salmon rest for 2-3 minutes before serving."
  ],
